This program was authorized in <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">19XX</TIMEX> (by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">P.L. XX</ENAMEX>-XXX) to ease the
transition into other <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">civilian positions</ENAMEX> of skilled technical,
administrative, and managerial <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">personnel</ENAMEX> who are no longer needed
in certain <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC_DESC">shipyards</ENAMEX> because of declining orders for <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Navy</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT_DESC">ship</ENAMEX>
construction.
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Eligibility</ENAMEX> is limited to those who have been employed at
designated <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">shipyards</ENAMEX> for <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">at least 5 years</TIMEX>, but who are not yet
eligible for retirement benefits. <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">Participants</ENAMEX> receive intensive
counseling to help them develop individual transition plans. This
counseling is provided by a private job placement service under
contract. <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">Participants</ENAMEX> are then reimbursed <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">up to $5,000</NUMEX> per year
for <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">up to 2 years</TIMEX>, not to exceed <NUMEX TYPE="PERCENT">80 percent</NUMEX> of the cost of the cost
of tuition, fees, books, and other student materials required for
attendance at approved educational <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">institutions</ENAMEX>.
An additional increment of education or technical training is
expected to reduce the period of transitional unemployment and
increase <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">the subsequent</TIMEX> earnings of <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">participants</ENAMEX>.
